  Q    WHEN TO USE 
1- embed_documents(FOR LARGE DATA WE GAVE )
2- embed_query(FOR USER I/P)

### 2. USE CASE: embed_documents=== Use this for the "Knowledge Base" (PDFs, Databases, Text files)
                                     # Optimized for processing large batches of text at once.
library_vectors = embeddings.embed_documents([
    "Cloud computing allows on-demand access to resources.",
    "AWS Bedrock is a managed service for foundation models."
])

### 3. USE CASE: embed_query === Use this for the "User Question" (The search bar input)
                            # Optimized for short, single strings to find the best match in the library.
user_vector = embeddings.embed_query("What is AWS Bedrock?")

# 4. Result Check
print(f"# Docs Batch Size: {len(library_vectors)}")
print(f"# Query Dimension: {len(user_vector)}")
